  "title": "QS Manager (Quantity Surveyor, M&E)",
  "description": "<p><em>Our client, a well-established </em><em><strong>M&amp;E Contractor</strong></em><em>, is seeking a seasoned Quantity Manager to lead cost and contract management for their </em><em><strong>mechanical and electrical projects</strong></em><em>. This role is suited for professionals with a strong background in </em><em><strong>M&amp;E works.</strong></em></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Oversee the full spectrum of quantity surveying activities related to M&amp;E works, from pre-contract to final account.</li>\n  <li>Prepare detailed cost estimates, tender submissions, and bills of quantities for mechanical and electrical systems.</li>\n  <li>Evaluate subcontractor quotations and manage procurement and cost negotiations.</li>\n  <li>Monitor budgets, track variations, and handle progress claims and cost reporting.</li>\n  <li>Advise on contractual issues, commercial risks, and cost control strategies for M&amp;E projects.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in Quantity Surveying, Building Services, or a related field.</li>\n  <li>At least 5 years of <strong>quantity surveying</strong> experience in <strong>M&amp;E works.</strong></li>\n  <li>Strong knowledge of M&amp;E systems, tendering processes, and local pricing.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in cost estimation software and MS Excel.</li>\n  <li>Excellent analytical, negotiation, and communication skills.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p>\n<p>Registration: R1326740</p>",
